.TH "i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink" 9 "i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink \- Set the hardware bridge mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct nlmsghdr *nlh "  ","
.BI "u16 flags "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack *extack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the netdev being configured
.IP "nlh" 12
RTNL message
.IP "flags" 12
bridge flags
.IP "extack" 12
netlink extended ack
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Inserts a new hardware bridge if not already created and
enables the bridging mode requested (VEB or VEPA). If the
hardware bridge has already been inserted and the request
is to change the mode then that requires a PF reset to
allow rebuild of the components with required hardware
bridge mode enabled.
.SH "NOTE"
expects to be called while under \fBrtnl_lock\fP
